The HD 89744 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 89744 is a star with 1.86 times the mass of the Sun, and 2.13 times its radius. It is located 126.01 light years away from the solar system.

HD 89744 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 89744 system


HD 89744 b

HD 89744 b was discovered by the Fred Lawrence Whipple Observatory observatory, in 2000-04, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.92 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 89744 b is 2655.300 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 89744 b is 12.600 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 89744 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
